<br>
<font size="+2">Information on the i&gt;clicker</font></span></font><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
</div>
<br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
<span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br>
To gauge in-class participation, I will partly rely on the i&gt;clicker response system from the </span><span style="font-style: italic; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">third week </span><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">of class onwards. If you want to receive bonus points for your in-class participation, I recommended that you buy a new or used </span><a style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;" href="http://www.addall.com/New/submitNew.cgi?query=9780716779391&amp;type=ISBN&amp;location=10000&amp;state=CA&amp;dispCurr=USD">i&gt;clicker</a><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"> or i</span><a style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;" href="http://www.addall.com/New/submitNew.cgi?query=978-1429280471&amp;type=ISBN&amp;location=10000&amp;state=CA&amp;dispCurr=USD">&gt;clicker2</a><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"> remote, or rent or borrow one, and then </span><a style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;" href="http://www.iclicker.com/support/registeryourclicker/">register</a><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
it using the same name and student ID as that on the UCI Registrar&#8217;s
student roster. It&#8217;s OK to share an iClicker with a friend who is not
enrolled in this class.</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
<br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
<span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Hardware Tips:</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
<ul style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
  <li>Pull the plastic tab from the back of your remote before use to
activate the batteries! All remotes have a 200 hour battery life, so
this should last a full quarter or more.</li>
  <li>Red flashing "low battery" light means 10 hours still remaining.
To change batteries (3 AAA), place a pen cap in the battery notch.</li>
</ul>
